<br>
The Wizard Alternate Advancement ability Improved Familiar has been upgraded on the Test Server.<br>
Currently this ability only gives the Wizard an extra 25 to all resists and See Invisible.<br>
<br>
The revised version on Test, in addition to the resists and see invisible components, now increases the Wizards mana by 200, adds 6 extra mana regeneration per tick and reduces the chance of Wizards spells fizzling or being resisted.<br>
<br>
Note: This is of course only on the Test server and may change before going live. <br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Who has more worthless AAexp then magicians? I mean our AAexp suck ass for lack of a better word. We can't even get them to increase the duration on our elemental forms but they are giving wizards clarity on there familiar and +200mana?????WTF!!!!!!! in addition to the uber resist, yet we can't even get our duration on water form increased. We can't get any better mana regen on our elemental forms or any worthwhile AAexp experiences. Maybe if Quick Summoning worked with our nukes that would be on par with manaburn and dire charm maybe. The imbalance and lack of mage concerns are really getting to me. I have tried to be patient but how much longer must we wait.<br>
<br>
Wezloc<br>
