fact #1) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> trans rods are 3.3 mana/tic</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (see below for calculations):<br>
-first calculate L60 mage hp regen.<br>
1.7 (1 standing 1 sitting, they wont be sitting all the time but they will most of the time hense the 1.7 assumption) + 5 (tpp) + 3 (aaxp) = 9.7 (total).<br>
-trans rods take 900 hp. 900/9.7 = 92.8. this means every 92.8 tics, a mage reaps the total mana regen benefits of trans rods.<br>
-trans rods cost 400m pre spec, and 348m post spec(13% savings which is the rumor i heard). they give back 312 net mana total.<br>
***so***<br>
312 (mana)/92.8 (tics) = 3.3 mana/tic regen<br>
<br>
fact #2) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> tpp is 3 mana/tic</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
fact #3) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> water form is 4 mana/tic</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 3.3 + 3 + 4 = 10.3 mana/tic</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for an aaxp 60 mage.<br>
---------------------------------------<br>
wizzies:<br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2 from their sheild</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 6 from their familiar</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2+6 = 8 mana/tic</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for an aaxp 60 wizard<br>
<br>
---------------------------------------<br>
other things to consider:<br>
-wizards <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> do not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> benefit in sustained dps from hp regen items the way mages do (unless there is a mage around to help them out). and as any caster will tell you, hp regen is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> much</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> easier to come by than mana regen. (zland heart, spirit wracked cords, aaxp are just a few off the top of my head which are moderately easy to obtain.)<br>
<br>
-mages do<br>
<br>
sorry but as of right this second mages &gt; wizards in mana regen, and this change is not a shaft to us nor overpowering.<br>
